HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 621
By Grills
A RESOLUTION to honor Marilyn and Vernon Holmes for their
contributions to the Dyer County Archives.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
recognize and honor individuals who have given selflessly of their time, talents, and convictions
to preserve and promote the foundational values that strengthen our families, communities, and
nation; and
WHEREAS, over the past twelve years, Marilyn and Vernon Holmes have made
invaluable contributions to the Dyer County Archives, ensuring that county records will be
available and easily accessible for generations to come; and
WHEREAS, Marilyn Holmes has served as the archives' first permanent archivist since
the formation of the Public Records Commission, demonstrating unwavering dedication and
excellence throughout her tenure; and
WHEREAS, as archivist, she has collaborated closely with the Public Records
Commission to determine which documents should be preserved and which could be
deaccessioned, resulting in the preservation of the majority of Dyer County records; and
WHEREAS, Marilyn and Vernon Holmes have proven to be an exceptional team,
investing a significant time in the damp basement beneath the Election Commission,
meticulously cleaning books, flattening papers, and conducting a comprehensive inventory of
records; and
WHEREAS, during challenging moments, such as when a newly renovated county office
was struggling under the weight of oversized books, both Marilyn and Vernon Holmes chose to
remain committed to their work despite the uncertainty surrounding the building's stability; with
the opening of the latest location, they have worked tirelessly to establish an efficient
