workspace, consistently exceeding expectations and even involving their grandchildren, who
were visiting from St. Louis, Missouri, in the operation; and
WHEREAS, Marilyn Holmes dedicates a significant amount of her time assisting
individuals of all backgrounds with their research needs, while Vernon Holmes contributes as a
computer technician for the archives and has utilized his engineering skills to develop a detailed
plan for the optimal layout of the new workspace; and
WHEREAS, Marilyn and Vernon Holmes have given freely of their time and talents to
enhance the Dyer County Archives, a tremendous gift to their contemporaries and future
residents alike; and
WHEREAS, it is both right and fitting that their remarkable public service be recognized
and celebrated; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor Marilyn and Vernon Holmes for their many contributions to the
Dyer County Archives, extending our gratitude for their devotion to serving their community and
preserving the history of the place they call home.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
